   <abstract >The Ramos Mariachi Violin Method treatise is an overview of Books 1 and 2 of an original violin teaching method. These method books teach violin and Spanish language vocal technique through carefully paced mariachi and Spanish language children's songs. Each song serves a pedagogical function and teaches incrementally paced violin skills such as bow strokes, left hand finger dexterity, sound quality, bow articulation, rhythm, and intonation. In addition to teaching violin pedagogy, the Ramos Mariachi Violin Method prepares the student to sing and perform violin on each song. Upon completing this method's series of books, the violin student will have developed a solid foundation of violin skills that fosters the musicianship and technical proficiency that is essential to violin playing. In addition, these same students will learn to sing Spanish language mariachi songs, preparing them with the ensemble and vocal skills necessary to sing and play mariachi music with a full band. In this way, students can learn to play the violin, while simultaneously celebrating mariachi music and Mexican culture.</abstract>
